    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-14T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/1178: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-15T00:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 15, 1939—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received December
                        16—12:41a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>434. Department’s circular December 15, 1 p.m. Aranha approves “as far as it
                    goes” but feels strongly that this should be only a preliminary step toward
                    stronger action as set out in his first suggestion of my 432, December 15, 2
                    p.m.</p>
                <p>He talked on the telephone this afternoon with Cantilo<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d125fn19">José M. Cantilo, Argentine Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> who is in general agreement with his attitude.</p>
                <p>Aranha says he expects arrival here tomorrow of English <hi rend="italic"
                        >Renown</hi> and an aircraft carrier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
